maps.Behind each Survo graphics window there isan enhanced metafile.This technique permits free scaling andexporting graphs to other environmentswithout losing accuracy.Each Survo graphics window can be moved,resized, minimized, and maximized by the mouse.The first three graphs are plotted again andyou may try to move and rescale themby the standard means of the Windows systemusing the mouse.ü.±TW10@TEXTS=T1 T1=[Arial(70)][BOLD][GREEN],Graph_1,200,150 OUTFILE=A1GPLOT /FRAMETW10@€TW30@.±TW10@TEXTS=T1 T1=[Arial(70)][BOLD][YELLOW],Graph_2,200,150 OUTFILE=A2GPLOT /FRAMETW10@€TW20@.±TW10@TEXTS=T1 T1=[Arial(70)][BOLD][RED],Graph_3,200,150 OUTFILE=A3GPLOT /FRAMETW10@€TW50@Ta-1@Tp        To continue, press ENTER! (or click this line!)@TVC1200@_@@Tp@üThus after such modificationsthe setup of graphs would be this!TW20@üTa1@Lo.±GPLOT /DEL ALL€BGPLOT FILE A1 / WHOME=WX/3,0 WSIZE=300*WX/1024,225*WY/768Ta-1@TW10@€Ta1@üBüGPLOT FILE A2 / WHOME=500*WX/1024,WY/5 WSIZE=WY/2,WY/2Ta-1@TW10@€Ta1@üBüGPLOT FILE A3 / WHOME=800*WX/1024,300*WY/768                WSIZE=300*WX/1024,400*WY/768Ta-1@TW10@€Ta1@üBL0üTa-1@TW60@üGPLOT /DEL ALLTW10@€TW10@TW30@üT!1@C2@TL!GP-NEXT@TXE@Tÿ
