0@€TW10@345678TW10@€€€€€€Tp        To continue, press ENTER! (or click this line!)@TVC600@_@@Tp@.±üüüGPLOT /DEL ALLTW10@€TW10@üT!1@C6@TL!GP-NEXT@TXE@Tÿ
















üüTa1@büTgC1@C1@C!@C1@C1@INIT 1000,100,100€üSYSTEM SAVE€BüGPLOT /LAYOUT SUR_G3.SYS€BüGPLOT /DEL ALL€BüTb0@ü   µµµµµµµ Overlaying graphs in SURVO MM In Survo it has been a long tradition that more complicatedpictures are created simply by overlaying two or more graphs.Overlaying is achieved by using INFILE and OUTFILE specifications.INFILE=<name_of_enhanced_meta_file>in a GPLOT scheme saves the current graph in a metafile.OUTFILE=<name_of_enhanced_meta_file>in a GPLOT scheme plots at first the metafile selected by OUTFILEand the current plot will be drawn over this basis.üTp        To continue, press ENTER! (or click this line!)@Ta-1@TVC600@_@@Tp@ü.±üExample:TW10@Putting two graphs in the same window "side by side"TW10@First graph:TW10@MODE=SVGA (i.e. 800x600)TW20@SIZE=400,600 HOME=0,0   specifying size and home within the windowTW20@LINETYPE=[RED][line_width(5)]TW10@OUTFILE=A               saving the graph in metafile A.EMFTW20@GPLOT Y(X)=X+C / C=-5,5,1TW20@€TW30@.±Second graph:TW10@MODE=SVGA (i.e. 800x600)TW10@SIZE=400,600 HOME=µ400µµµµµµµ,0TW20@LINETYPE=[BLUE][line_width(5)]TW10@INFILE=A               taking A.EMF as the basisTW20@GPLOT Y(X)=-X+C / C=-5,5,1TW20@€TW30@ü.±TW10@Of course the same graphs can be plottedover each other:TW20@COPY CUR-8,CUR-4,CURTW20@€TW20@TW10@TW20@TW10@€TW30@.±TW10@In a similar way any number ofSURVO MM screen graphs can beoverlaid.TW20@Let's plot a third one over the previous ones.TW20@First the combination of those twomust be saved by OUTFILE.TW20@TW10@OUTFILE=ATW20@TW20@TW10@€TW20@TW10@Now the third plot is definedand plotted over:TW20@MODE=SVGASIZE=400,600 HOME=0,0LINETYPE=[YELLOW][line_width(5)]INFILE=A OUTFILE=ATW20@GPLOT Y(X)=C / C=-5,5,1TW20@€TW30@.±TW10@Because the combination of allthree plots was saved in metafile A.EMF,TW10@ it can beplotted afterwards simply as follows:TW20@GPLOT /DEL ALLTW20@€TW10@GPLOT FILE ATW10@€TW20@GPLOT /DEL ALLTW10@€TW10@üT!1@C5@TL!GP-NEXT@TXE@Tÿ









