üüTa1@büTgC1@C1@C!@C1@C1@INIT 1000,100,100€üSYSTEM SAVE€BüGPLOT /LAYOUT SUR_G3.SYS€BüGPLOT /DEL ALL€BüTb0@ü   µµµµµµµ Control commands for SURVO MM screen graphics As explained already in preceding sections, each graphics window ofSURVO MM can be freely moved, resized, minimized maximized, anddeleted by the mouse.Modifications can be done also by special GPLOT control commands.These are useful tools especially when making graphical applicationsof Survo as sucros.GPLOT /DEL ALLcloses all existing SURVO MM graphics windows.GPLOT /DEL <number>closes the window having the given number in its title bar.GPLOT /SHOW MIN <number>minimizes the given Survo graphics window.GPLOT /SHOW NORMAL <number>restores the window to its earlier size and position (after /SHOW MIN)GPLOT /SHOW MAX <number>maximizes the given Survo graphics window.Tp        To continue, press ENTER! (or click this line!)@Ta-1@TVC1200@_@@Tp@Ta1@üGPLOT /NEXT <integer>selects the next graphics window to be the one with the order <integer>in the current layout.GPLOT /PREVselects the previous graphics window for the next graph. This command(with IN- and OUTFILE specifications) provides a simple way formaking overlay graphics (in sucros).GPLOT /FIX <integer>selects a fixed graphics window with order <integer> for all subsequentgraphs. This command is helpful in the same way as GPLOT /PREV.GPLOT /FIRST <integer>limits rotation of graphics windows. For example, if # of windows(according the current layout) is 8 and GPLOT /FIRST 5 is activated,the windows of subsequent GPLOT's will be rotating according tosequence 5,6,7,8,5,6,7,8,5,6,7,8,... thus leaving windows 1,2,3,4intact.Tp        To continue, press ENTER! (or click this line!)@Ta-1@TVC600@_@@Tp@.±Using GPLOT control commands (examples):TW10@We select the layout SUR_G8.SYS.TW10@GPLOT /LAYOUT SUR_G8.SYSTD2@€TD0@Plotting 9 graphs by starting from window 5:TW10@GPLOT /NEXT 5TD2@€TD0@GPLOT /FRAME / TEXTS=T T=[Arial(70)],Graph_1,200,150TD2@€TD0@SET CUR+1,CUR+8,CUR-1TW10@€TW20@TW5@TW5@23456789TW10@TW10@TW10@€TW10@€TW10@€TW30@TW10@€TW20@TW10@€TW10@€TW10@€TW10@üPlease note that next graph (9) deletes (1):TW20@üTW10@[RED]TW10@üTW10@€TW30@ü.±Plotting to a fixed window 4:GPLOT /FIX 4TD2@€TD0@GPLOT Y(X)=10*SIN(X)TD2@€TD0@Doing the same using WSIZE and WHOME:TW20@WSIZE=WX/3,WY/3 WHOME=WX-WX/3,0TW20@TW10@€TW20@.±Again to window 4 without WSIZE and WHOME:TW15@GPLOT Y(X)=10*SIN(X)TW10@€TW20@.±Using GPLOT /FIX several times:TW15@GPLOT /FIX 7TD2@€TD0@GPLOT Y(X)=XTD2@€TD0@GPLOT /FIX 3TD2@€TD0@GPLOT Y(X)=-XTD2@€TD0@Thus any of the graphics windows may bereplotted when needed.TW10@This is a useful feature especiallyin sucros made for graphical applications.TW30@ü.±The /FIX setting is deleted only byGPLOT /DEL ALL and GPLOT /NEXT commands.TW30@TW10@Using the GPLOT /FIRST command:TW10@At first the /FIX setting is deleted byGPLOT /NEXT 1TW20@€TW10@We are going to keep windows 1,2,3,4 intactTW10@and let the new graphs rotate in windows5,6,7,8.TW30@ Therefore we give the commandGPLOT /FIRST 5TW20@€TW10@and start plotting more graphs:TW20@GPLOT /FRAME / TEXTS=T T=[ArialB(70)],Plot_1,200,150TW10@TW10@SET CUR+2,CUR+9,CUR+1TW10@€TW20@TW10@23456789TW10@TW10@TW10@TW10@PEN=[WHITE] COLORS=[WHITE][/BLUE]TW10@TW10@€TW20@TW10@€TW10@TW10@€TW10@TW10@€TW20@TW10@€TW20@TW10@€TW10@TW10@€TW10@TW10@€TW10@TW10@€TW30@TW10@If a GPLOT /DEL ALL command is activated,TW10@it removes only the "rotating" windows:TW20@GPLOT /DEL ALLTW20@€TW20@To close all graphics windows of the currentSURVO MM session, we give the commandTW20@GPLOT /FIRST 1TW20@€TW10@and thenGPLOT /DEL ALLTW10@€TW30@üT!1@CX@TL!GP-NEXT@TXE@Tÿ














